    "lyrics": {
      "text": "O_ strange won-der! O dread mys-ter-y! He that by na-ture as God is im-mor-tal and can-not die, how is He hanged on a tree; can it be He doth taste of death? Is He con-demned,__ Who of all is in-no-cent? Be-hold, O Sun,__ hide thy light and quake with fear at___ this au-dac-i-ty! Thus the Vir-gin spake with groans as she be-held hang-ing on the Cross the Sav-iour Christ, Whom she__ had__ borne."
    }
